window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Set in Colonial New England, </b><b><i>Slewfoot </i></b><b>is a tale of magic and mystery, of triumph and terror as only dark fantasist Brom can tell it. </b></p> <p>Connecticut, 1666.&nbsp;</p> <p>An ancient spirit awakens in a dark wood. The wildfolk call him Father, slayer, protector.&nbsp;</p> <p>The colonists call him Slewfoot, demon, devil.&nbsp;</p> <p>To Abitha, a recently widowed outcast, alone and vulnerable in her pious village, he is the only one she can turn to for help.&nbsp;</p> <p>Together, they ignite a battle between pagan and Puritan - one that threatens to destroy the entire village, leaving nothing but ashes and bloodshed in their wake.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p><b><i>“If it is a devil you seek, then it is a devil you shall have!” </i></b></p> <p><b>A Macmillan Audio production from Tor Nightfire</b></p>"; 
